      "writtenOn": "2020-08-22T07:57:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Status is an enum{}, and Protobuf doesn\u0027t allow unknown enum values.\n\nfrom https://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/docs/proto#enum\n\"a field with an enum type can only have one of a specified set of constants as its value (if you try to provide a different value, the parser will treat it like an unknown field.\"\n\n---------------\nUpdated to disallow ENDMASK.\n\nQ. the python implementation allows ENDMASK. Should we also fix the python validator to disallow ENDMASK?",
